gasoline PRICES 
Mr. David Chatters ( Athabasca , Ref. ) : 
Mr. Speaker , gas prices are getting a lot of attention these days . 
the truth is Canadians enjoy some of the lowest gas prices in the world . 
without government taxes , gas is as cheap as it was 20 years ago . 
the only thing that has changed dramatically is the amount Canadians are being taxed at the pumps . 
when I go into a grocery store or a restaurant I see the before tax price of the product . 
why can gas retailers not do the same for their customers ? 
why do retailers not advertise their gasoline prices on a before tax basis so Canadians can plainly see how much of their gas dollar is going into the government ' s tax tank ? 
why are gas retailers willing to take the heat for government taxation ? 
Canadians need tax cuts now so they can get more distance for their dollar . 
