what is important is that these northern communities have , from time immemorial , maintained a close relationship with the land and its resources . 
their traditional economy is based on the bounty of nature and the land , for instance boots made of skins , bone and ivory needles , food - gathering , trapping , and so forth . 
in addition to providing for the material needs of the Labrador Inuit and Innu , the land is at the heart of their relationship with other works of the Creator , and their spirituality . 
